# gh-review-tool — optional environment configuration
#
# This tool does NOT require any environment variables.
# Authentication is handled entirely by:
#   - the gh CLI (run `gh auth login` once)
#   - your AI provider's own CLI (opencode auth, claude login, etc.)
#
# Optional:
#
# Selects which AI backend to use. Supported values: opencode, claude-code.
# Defaults to opencode when unset.
# AI_PROVIDER=opencode
#
# The following variables are intentionally stripped from every subprocess
# environment so that child processes use the gh CLI's keyring auth instead
# of inheriting a token:
#   GITHUB_TOKEN  (removed automatically if set)
#   GH_TOKEN      (removed automatically if set)
#
# This prevents accidental token leakage into opencode, claude, git, or any
# other subprocess the app spawns.
